column1: Mobile: Shipping fee is not calculated correctly in case of multiple packages
column30:
h4. *Prerequisite:* 

OSF-Shipping fee is configered/set to 6.99 € in GASO 
h3. Observations in SIT

*Test 1* : Simple Order (ACQ Mobile package incl. HW, delivery to legal- or alternate delivery address)
{color:#172b4d}*Result*{color}: {color:#00875a}Shipping cost is set to 6.99 €{color}

*Test 2* : Multiproposition (Order 2 ACQ Mobile packages incl. HW, delivery to legal- or alternate delivery address)
{*}Result{*}:{color:#de350b} Shipping is cost is 0,00 € for each package{color}
*Expected result:* Shipping cost is 6.99 € for each package

!https://confluence.sp.vodafone.com/download/attachments/485738063/image-2024-1-23_11-30-5.png?version=1&modificationDate=1706005817699&api=v2!

 

 

Date : 31/Jan/2024

As per internal investigation done in Omnius solution and identified as below.

According to wave4 PDT epic (ref Epic screen below) 

conclusion : Omnius trigger GASO service per package and later based on per package response,  shipping fee would be shown over UI 
either standard service delievry  or via service delivery option.(i..e UPS/GLS`/UPS)

After selection of service delivery,  Omnius add static sku in Shopping cart with shipping fee value.
(i..e shippingfee) where this shipping fee send to backend via processorder/submitOrder request xml.

 

 

*Note: In case of multiple mobile package having multiple shippe fee, then Omnius must set shipping fee for package which has highest shipping fee value  and rest package shipping fee must be considerd as 0.00.(no charge) :*

 

Issue identified
 # {color:#00875a}Mobile (single package) : working fine.{color}
 # In case of multiple Mobile : this seems not wokring correctly. even highest shipping fee price for shippigfee sku not show w over UI (order summary and order overview page), currently show 0.0 for all mobile packages.
 # {color:#00875a}Cable : system is not calling GASO service and there is no need to show this shippingfee sku for cable package.  Currently PCAT sku (V3K)  is shown with price Order sumamry also in shoppingcart.  working fine{color}
 # {color:#de350b}DSL (single package in Order) : system is calling GASO service and there is not show this shippingfee sku for DSL package. Currently PCAT sku (10004)  is shown with price Order sumamry also in shoppingcart.  ? *need to check with VF*{color}
 # {color:#de350b}MPO (MOB and DSL): *need to check with VF*{color}

 

 

*EPIC description* 

!image-2024-01-31-14-07-50-394.png!

column1113:
07/Dec/23 3:38 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;I checked the logs provided and don't think this is a cable issue, or at least that we need more information to debug it.

The image provided shows an error message that is usually triggered by so called "compatibility rules", rules provided by us, but executed by the OSE rules engine.

The error message starts with "Es ist nur möglich 0 produkte" which usually means it is triggered by a compatibility rule with the operation "MAX(0)". The conditions of all rules with this operation are:
{code:java}
  serviceSourceExpression: cart.containsProduct('UNITYPREVENTIONKIP')
  serviceSourceExpression: cart.containsProduct('UNITYPREVENTIONTV')
  serviceSourceExpression: cart.containsProduct('3PDROPREQUIREDKIP') and !cart.containedProductInCategory('CABLE->CABLE_TV->SKY')
  serviceSourceExpression: cart.containsProduct('3PDROPREQUIREDTV') and !cart.containedProductInCategory('CABLE->CABLE_INTERNET_PHONE->3P Vorteil')
  serviceSourceExpression: cart.containsProduct("UMEKUDBLOCKER")
  serviceSourceExpression: cart.containsProduct("KIPCHANGEDMARKERFORKUD") and !cart.containsProduct("KIPOPENEDMARKER")
  serviceSourceExpression: cart.containsProduct("KUDCHANGEDMARKERFORKIP") and !cart.containsProduct("KUDOPENEDMARKER")
  serviceSourceExpression: '!cart.containsProduct("OMNIUSTVCHANGEDMARKER")'
  serviceSourceExpression: '!cart.containsProduct("OMNIUSKIPCHANGEDMARKER")'
  serviceSourceExpression: '!cart.containsProduct("OMNIUSKUDCHANGEDMARKER")'
  serviceSourceExpression: cart.containsNbaIndicator("KIP-TW") and !cart.package.isTariffChanged(){code}
According to the logs the cart does not contain UNITYPREVENTIONKIP, UNITYPREVENTIONTV, 3PDROPREQUIREDKIP, 3PDROPREQUIREDTV, UMEKUDBLOCKER, KIPCHANGEDMARKERFORKUD, KUDCHANGEDMARKERFORKIP.

This leaves us with the 4 conditions:
{code:java}
serviceSourceExpression: '!cart.containsProduct("OMNIUSTVCHANGEDMARKER")'   serviceSourceExpression: '!cart.containsProduct("OMNIUSKIPCHANGEDMARKER")'   serviceSourceExpression: '!cart.containsProduct("OMNIUSKUDCHANGEDMARKER")'
serviceSourceExpression: cart.containsNbaIndicator("KIP-TW") and !cart.package.isTariffChanged() {code}
Of which the first three seem likely to trigger the message as they are not present in the cart according to the log.

These products however should be selected automatically if anything changed in the package.
I also noticed that in the screenshot and in the logs you have "01H:B06" selected, which is not actually a valid product anymore with the product setup version V2310_2023_11_00_088.

This lets me believe that the issue is with a mismatch between the cable rules plugin version you are executing and the cable rules plugin version expected be the product configuration you have imported. Thankfully our logs contain the cable rules plugin information as well and according to the logs you are executing a cable rules plugin from version V2270_2023_07_00_038_D02.;;;

column1114:
22/Nov/23 1:32 PM;gaurav.chauhan4@vodafone.com;Hi All,

This issue is solved now in SIT1.

I knew from our tester,  someone is changing product configuration(product visibility) using backoffice. Ideally that must not be done if one is not aware about what side effect it can create and what is the ideal way of doing it.
If we do any config change from Backoffice then we must clean the redis cache else for sure will have inconsistent result and inconsistency in cachings. Such manual PCAT changes ideally must not be done using BO, if it’s required as per the business need then changes should come via raw PCAT files. If changes are for temporary test, then as I said after change must need to clean redis and varnish cache to avoid any inconsistency in caching.

Imo this is the RC of this issue. So, if someone is doing then please avoid it or do the cache clean properly and then see if such issue comes again.
;;;

23/Nov/23 12:36 PM;pallavi.chaudhari1@vodafone.com;Received below update from Robert 

We have discussed Vodafone internally and came to the conclusion, that we have a design gap / bug in epic OS-9066:

We have created  in this Epic a new customer type:  SOHO TYPE S with SK  / (  CustomerType =  “SOHO”  CustomerSubType = “RVPRIVATE”

In order for OSF to show  in the configurator the cable  products that are available at a certain address for THIS customer type, OSF must request the cable PLugIn  and inform the cable plugin about the customer type.

The customer type in cable plugin is called:  “LEGAL_PERSON”

WE DID NOT CONSIDER THIS
 * [@Shruti  Kanchan|mailto:SK00790019@Dynacommerce.com]  todo ASAP:  we need a correction in the software/ new user-story in Epic OS-9066 :   If customertype = SOHO TYPE S with RV, then call cable PlugInn with customer_type “LEGAL_PERSON”;;;

As per the *OS-39387* –

 

“If the Flag MaxCust is set to 'YES' then,

 
 * Enhance the system to Modify the "WARENKOERBE & ANGEBOTE" functionality in the 360View to restrict the loading of the shopping carts and offers based on loaded subscribers from the mode 2 response.

column1: INT - Testplan || CR690 || OSF Sky Migration / Integrate secrets management tool (Harshicorp Vault) for Sky delivery (VFSWTQ00042911)
column30:
This request needs to be placed as CR to vendor Amdocs for further processing (estimating costs and ordering for implementation).

This CR defines the technical requirements for integration of a secrets management tool, here 3rd party tool Harshicorp Vault, from Amdocs side. This tool will be used with Sky application delivery process and CI/CD pipeline in the future. The goal is to manage the handling of credentials in the pipeline by separation of passwords from Amdocs delivery. The credentials are stored securely in secrets management tool, that only the environment responsibles (persons/roles) can view and control the credentials for a target environment.

CR target date is R7.2 release / *GoLive 12.2.2023* (PROD security demand).

Amdocs analyzed, that integration of secrets management tool is do-able, but require many code changes so Amdocs will require CR to start the work. Technical requirements to be implemented by Amdocs:
 * REQ-01: Setting some template to use for the 3 secrets required
 * REQ-02: Access to vault (probably requires some authentication) on helm script. 
 * REQ-03: Getting the secrets (probably retrieved via ArgoCD vault plugin resp. API)
 * REQ-04: Parsing the secrets into yamls. Refer to documentation Url [https://argocd-vault-plugin.readthedocs.io/en/stable/]
 * REQ-05: Deploy the secrets
 * REQ-06: Checking all references for secrets in Amdocs code to make sure no changes required
 * REQ-07: New secrets management solution should be documented within credential/certicates renewal process

 

+Note (A.Kulkarni):+ Kubernetes configuration for Harshicorp Vault integration requires to replace the ArgoCD interface with the ArgoCD Vault interface. Can be provided on short term.

+Note (Y.Majeti):+ CR requires dedicated SIT+ACC environment for implementation and testing including vault integration.

It was commited, that Amdocs shall start CR process with cost estimation / feasibility date. Any impediments caused by non-availabiliy of environments need to be evaluated during CR execution and may result in timeline correction.
